		<td><b>Final fantasy XIII</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For those that still follow the serie, a demo of Final Fantasy XIII was made available in japan with the FFVII advent children complete bluray movie.
<br />
<br />I had a chance to play it.  If you didn't like the fighting system from XII (I'm one of those), you will be rejoiced to know that they changed it.  It feel a little bit like the older ones but completely real time, except it has been quite simplified a lot. 
<br />
<br />No more magic point, you have a gauge that fills up that allow you do to action. You chain some action up to three at the same time.  You don't have to wait for the gauge to be filled since it's separated in 3 parts so this mean you can launch between 1 to 3 actions depending on the status of it.
<br />
<br />The graphics are nice, I can't say anything about that.  It was quite simplified but I enjoyed it.  Anybody else had the chance to try it?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


