		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah the "battle system" of FF12 doesn't really have appeal and the game has basically nothing in commun with the first 10 titles which make me wonder why they even called it "Final Fantasy". It looks more like a spinoff of FF Tactics to me instead of a part of the main series (which is in my opinion dead since 2001 pas the release of FF10). Square keep releasing crappy remakes and one in a while a mediocre new game with awesome graphics.
<br />
<br />I have to say the FF12 is not an entierely crappy game it's playable and have really nice graphics (I especially like the optionnal "interlace filter" that you can enable, it is one of the only PS2 games I have that looks smooth on my old TV and that is not flickering). The music is not entierely bad altough it sounds more like FF Tactics to me. But still they artificially pasted the title "Final Fantasy" on this game, and make it like an offline MMO and I just don't like MMOs, even if they are ofline.
<br />
<br />Yet I have to admit that the automatic battle stuff is practical to read courses while playing at the same time.

		

