<br />Well, on the original Playstation and on the PS2 if you don't have enought space on the memory card you can play the game but you can't save. Do you find that retarded ? At least saves are hadly ever lost as opposed to Nintendo cartridge based games. But again you can scratch discs, not carts.
<br />
<br />Yes FFXI is probably what marked the discontinuity. Among most FF fans, nobody played that, they all switched to this dumb Wow game and became no-lives, and now I'm the only FF fan arround  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /> 
<br />Then again Celius, in order for you to say FFX2 sucks you'd first have to play it (borrow it don't buy it). You don't have to beat it, but in order to say something is bad it's logical you have to play it, even if pretty much everyone says so.
<br />
<br />Oh, and while FFX-2 and FF12 sucks because of their discontinuity and retardement as opposed to previous games, FF2 on the NES sucks even more because of it's horrible battle system and item/spell limitation system. Bad gameplay is worse than bad design after all.
<br />
<br />And Final Fantasy Mystic Quest is great, but it's really a spin-off, and have almost no story, and the battle system is more like Dragon Quest games. So if you have played all FFs, you may enjoy it less than I did when it was the second FF I've ever played (first being FF7).

		

